729610f-a.folder: Sand Lane & Oceanside Avenue, Staten Island, NY
729610f-a.text:
Sand Lane, south from Oceanside Avenue (at the railroad tracks) to Seaside Boulevard. Shown is the business
center and bath houses of South Beach.
June 2, 1935
P. L. Sperr

729611f-a.text:
Sand Lane, east side, near Oceanside Avenue (at the railroad tracks), showing a bungalow colony at South
Beach.
June 2, 1935
P. L. Sperr
